Lugari MP Ayub Savula has asked Kenyans to welcome the People’s Assembly approach to ensure justice for all. He said NASA will use the law to eject President Uhuru Kenyatta from power and instal opposition chief Raila Odinga. “NASA has started the constitutional amendment journey that will ensure the will of the people is respected and their votes count. This will end this circle of crisis every election year,” Savula said. He spoke in Kakamega town on Monday. NASA has drafted a motion for the establishment of the People’s Assembly The motion has been tabled in 19 counties for debate and approval. Siaya, Homa Bay and Vihiga counties approved the motion last week. One of the resolutions MCAs are supposed to approve says the August 8 and October 26 presidential elections were invalid, null and void.